  <section class="research-survey-design">
    <div class="main-grid">
      <h2>Survey Design</h2>
      <div class="first">
        <p>The survey was designed to be easy and engaging to complete. It was also <b>designed with the assumption that
            the participant may not know anything about the IndieWeb.</b></p>

        <p>There were three sections to this survey:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><b>Demographic questions</b> (age, gender, and profession)</li>
          <li><b>Questions relating to social media</b> (usage habits and thoughts)</li>
          <li><b>Questions surrounding IndieWeb and decentralised social media</b> (a text and video section explaining
            the concepts, thoughts on these technologies and questions about website ownership)</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <link-button class="bg-yellow orange"
        href="https://docs.google.com/forms/u/1/d/1viJ_Ymr4RCEm3I5wBqfPGyjpF3rKaOyrXoghaQpSuus/edit">
        <p slot="text" class="text-center">Click here for a live copy of the survey with the questions and sections!</p>
      </link-button>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="research-paragraph-section">
    <div class="main-grid">
      <paragraph-block class="bg-white">
        <div slot="paragraph" class="">
          <p>In total, there were <b>97 survey participants</b> from various age groups. </p>

          <p>Using snowball sampling methods unfortunately leads to the tendency for participants to recruit people
            sharing similar traits (<a
              href="https://www.medwave.cl/revisiones/revisiontemas/8513.html?_view=en">Navarrete, et al.</a>, 2022).
          </p>

          <p>Most of the participants were working in technology (47.4%) and design (23.7%).</p>

          <p>It’s very like that this is due to my background in design and the sharing of the survey through the
            IndieWeb community. 68% of participants identified as male, and 28.1% identified as female.</p>

          <p>It would be great to re-conduct this survey at a later date with a wider sample range for greater diversity
            and more accurate results.</p>
        </div>
      </paragraph-block>
      </half-half>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="on-social-media">
    <div class="main-grid">
