      <div class="first" slot="first">
        <h2>On social media</h2>
        <p><b>Generally, survey participants had an unfavourable opinion of social media.</b></p>

        <p>Sentimental analysis of long-form replies showed that people were largely concerned/dissatisfied with:</p>
        <ol>
        <li>The <b>proliferation of advertisements</b> and the apps being increasingly profit-driven (23/60)</li>
        <li><b>Addictive qualities</b> of social media apps (16/60)</li>
        <li><b>Privacy and security</b> concerns (15/60)</li>
        </ol>
      <p>Meanwhile, the biggest reason for remaining on social media apps is due to friends and family being on mainstream social media. (<a href="/critique">See more results here</a>)</p>
      </div>
      <big-quote class="transparent" slot="second">
        <p class="quote" slot="quote">
          “The algorithms prey on people's addictive temperaments for profit. I find myself entering a feedback loop of dopamine stimulation a lot, aka doom-scrolling.”
        </p>
        <p class="attribution" slot="attribution">A survey participant aged 25–30 who isn’t a part of the IndieWeb</p>
      </big-quote>
    </half-half>
  </div>
